page.title: 09FISHY INFLUENCES
page.content: Heading northward, a few hundred metres from our school is Agnew Park. This is a children's play area with swings, see-saw, climbing frame, hobby horse, chute, maypole,and infant swings.Here you can also have a game of putting,crazy golf,or draughts. Next to the park is The Marine Lake.This is a man made boating pool and swimming area.There is now windsurfing,sailing,rowing, and paddle boats in the Marine Lake. Bordering the Marine Lake on the east side is the West Pier and the Harbour.Clustered around the harbour are the streets; Fisher Street,Market Street,Harbour Street and Kipper Lane.These streets, now offices and garages, were once inhabited by seafaring folk.Indeed the beginning of Agnew Cresc.,we found from old maps, was once called Neptune Place.
